<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3080a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-25T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                        1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Department is with difficulty restraining responsible press comment
                            here on the Tientsin affair and is doubtful how long it may be able to
                            do so owing to the numerous circumstantial reports arriving in the
                            United States through papers published in China and Japan. An early
                            settlement of the question is highly desirable. I have spoken to Ishii
                            in the same sense.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>